Cell.Text: Do you have a moment to talk?

Node.Caption: DLC1VQ04RNPCStartBranchTopic: Are you trying to get my attention?

Cell.Text: Didn't want that lot getting wind of it. Especially my father.
Half the people in your little crew would just as soon kill me as talk to me. | That doesn't exactly make me want to open up. | I got a warmer welcome from my father, and that's saying something.

Node.Caption: DLC1VQ04RNPCStartBranchTopic01: Why didn't you say something earlier?

Node.ToolTip:
01003C0E - Custom, in use by ananes
Last User:builds Date:3/26/2012 File:DLC01.esm

Cell.Text: It's not a question of trust... he's just obsessed with the prophecy. | And from what I could tell, a thousand extra years of obsession haven't made him any better. We should have found him a hobby.

Node.Caption: DLC1VQ04RNPCStartBranchTopic02b: Do you trust Harkon at all?

Cell.Text: Well, you could waste a lot of time trying to figure out our next move, or you could let me help. | Your choice.

Node.Caption: DLC1VQ04RNPCStartBranchTopic00a: Can't it wait?

Cell.Text: That Moth Priest, Dexion. He said we needed two other Elder Scrolls. I think I know where we can start looking.

Node.Caption: DLC1VQ04RNPCStartBranchTopic00b: What's on your mind?

Cell.Text: We need to find my mother. | She'll definitely know where it is, and if we're lucky, she actually has it herself.

Node.Caption: DLC1VQ04RNPCStartBranch02Topic: So where is this Elder Scroll?

Cell.Text: The last time I saw her, she said that she'd go somewhere safe... somewhere that my father would never search. | Other than that, she wouldn't tell me anything. | But the way she said it... "someplace he would never search." It was cryptic, yet she called attention to it.

Node.Caption: DLC1VQ04RNPCStartBranchTopic03: You said you didn't know where she went.

Cell.Text: Maybe. | What I can't figure out is why she said it that way.

Node.Caption: DLC1VQ04RNPCStartBranchTopic04: Sounds like she was being cautious.

Node.ToolTip:
01003C0B - Custom, in use by ananes
Last User:builds Date:3/26/2012 File:DLC01.esm

Cell.Text: Besides, I can't imagine a single place my father would avoid looking. And he's had all this time, too. | Any ideas?

Node.Caption: DLC1VQ04RNPCStartBranchTopic05

Cell.Text: S|They'd be even less welcoming to her than they've been to me. It would have been a bloodbath. | And since the Dawnguard are still around, that must not have happened. | Any other ideas?
S|I doubt my mother would waste her time with those fools. | They probably would have tried to kill her, and that has a way of souring relationships. | Any other ideas?

Node.Caption: DLC1VQ04RNPCStartBranchTopic06a: Hiding with the Dawnguard?

Cell.Text: They aren't going to let use the front door.
True. But I know a way we can get to the courtyard without arousing suspicion.
How can we get in without your father noticing?
Trust me. I lived in that castle for a very long time and I know every nook and cranny.

Node.Caption: DLC1VQ04RNPCStartBranchTopic07

Cell.Text: S|I don't think so. She said she wanted to stay awake in case the situation was resolved. | It had to be one of us, and, well, she's so much more powerful than I am. It just made sense for her to be out here. | Any other thoughts?

Node.Caption: DLC1VQ04RNPCStartBranchTopic06b: Sealed away like you were?

Cell.Text: Wait... that almost makes sense! There's a courtyard in the castle. I used to help her tend a garden there. | All of the ingredients for our potions came from there. She used to say that my father couldn't stand the place. Too... peaceful.

Node.Caption: DLC1VQ04RNPCStartBranchTopic06c: In Castle Volkihar?

Cell.Text: [S] There's an unused inlet on the northern side of the island that was used by the previous owners to bring supplies into the castle. | An old escape tunnel from the castle exits there. I think that's our way in.

Node.Caption: DLC1VQ04RNPCStartBranchTopic08

Cell.Text: Oh, absolutely. But my mother's not a coward. | That is... I don't think we'll actually trip over her there. But it's worth a look.

Node.Caption: DLC1VQ04RNPCStartBranchTopic06fin: Isn't that pretty risky, staying around the castle?

Cell.Text: [S] I don't think he even sees me as his daughter anymore. I'm just... a means to an end.

Node.Caption: DLC1VQ04RNPCStartBranchTopic02d

Cell.Text: Ever since father decided that pursuing the prophecy was his calling, we've drifted further and further apart.

Node.Caption: DLC1VQ04RNPCStartBranchTopic02a: What is it between you two?

Cell.Text: You know, I've been asking myself that very same question. | I was hoping seeing me again after all these years would stir something inside him, but apparently his obsession with the prophecy hasn't let up.

Node.Caption: DLC1VQ04RNPCStartBranchTopic02c: Does Harkon even care about you anymore?

Cell.Text: If you have a better lead than this, I'm all ears.

Node.Caption: DLC1VQ04RNPCStartBranchTopic04b: We can't waste time on cryptic clues.

Cell.Text: There's always that possibility. She seemed almost as obsessed as my father by the time she closed the lid on that sarcophagus. | But I can't worry about that now. We need the scroll, and she's our only lead.

Node.Caption: DLC1VQ04RNPCStartBranchTopic04c: Maybe your mother didn't trust you, either.
